inputs.description: A collection of arguments for invoking getIntent.

name.description: Name of the intent. The name is case sensitive.

outputs.description: A collection of values returned by getIntent.

checksum.description:
Checksum identifying the version of the intent that was created. The checksum is not
included as an argument because the resource will add it automatically when updating the intent.

createdDate.description: Date when the intent version was created.

id.description: The provider-assigned unique ID for this managed resource.

lastUpdatedDate.description: Date when the $LATEST version of this intent was updated.

name.description: Name of the intent, not case sensitive.

parentIntentSignature.description:
A unique identifier for the built-in intent to base this
intent on. To find the signature for an intent, see
[Standard Built-in Intents](https://developer.amazon.com/public/solutions/alexa/alexa-skills-kit/docs/built-in-intent-ref/standard-intents)
in the Alexa Skills Kit.
